{#- SECURITY — prose. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="trust-security">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Data security</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Your data stays yours. Always.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The single biggest data-security risk in outsourced bookkeeping is the <strong>parallel-system model</strong> &mdash; where a provider exports your financials into their own platform, leaving you without control of your own books. TechBrot doesn&rsquo;t work that way.</p>
      <p>We operate as an <strong>accountant-user inside your existing QuickBooks file</strong>. You grant access; you can revoke it at any time. Your books never leave your control. The QuickBooks audit trail records every action we take and remains visible to you continuously &mdash; you can see exactly what was changed, when, and by whom.</p>
      <p>All working sessions use <strong>encrypted screen-share connections</strong>; file transfers, when needed, use encrypted channels. We follow documented data-handling practices appropriate for sensitive financial information, detailed in our <a href="/legal/dpa/">data processing terms</a> and <a href="/legal/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a>.</p>
      <p>The principle is simple: <strong>you hold the keys.</strong> We&rsquo;re a credentialed professional working in your house, not a vendor who takes your house away to work on it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- SCOPE — 3 (baseline h3s: We do / We don't / We coordinate with). sand alt. -#}
